'''Tommaso Martini''' ([[Bivongi]], [[Calabria]], 1688 <U+2013> 5 January 1755) was an [[Italy|Italian]] painter of the late-[[Baroque]].

==Biography==
By1723, he had moved to Naples. He is said to have trained with [[Francesco Solimena]], and later under [[Luca Giordano]]. He was active in Naples and Rome.<ref>[http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/tommaso-martini_(Dizionario-Biografico)/ Encyclopedia Treccani], Dizionario Biografico degli Italiani - Volume 71 (2008), entry by Francesca Mangiola.</ref> He painted an altarpiece of <U+2018><U+2019>Virgin and Saints<U+2019><U+2019> for the church of Chiesa della SS. Trinit<U+00E0> in [[Petrizzi]].<ref>[http://www.scuole24ore.it/Article.aspx?ca=3801es00dz11wffocuogmeycv45596-74943 Scuole24 Ore] article on [[Petrizzi]] altarpiece.</ref>

